message: The golden rule: Do NOT add anything to an item once it has been framed, its value will become negative. message: To maximize your score, prioritize combining two base ingredients that have different origins (natural/artificial) but the same texture (soft/soft or hard/hard) for 30 points. If you use tools, only use 'scissors' on soft items for 25 points, as using them on hard items results in negative values. For example, combine a natural soft item (like mushroom) with an artificial soft item (like thread/yarn/paper) or a natural hard item (like wood) with an artificial hard item (like buttons/beads). These combinations consistently yield a value of 30. Then, use the 'frame' tool on this 30-value item to reliably reach a value of 50. Do not use the 'scissors' tool, as it tends to reduce value or make items negative. Also, do not modify a framed item further, as advised by a previous player, it will lead to negative points.
